From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: Add deterministic canvas pixel noise to getImageData

Under PureCloak, inject deterministic ±1 noise into ~0.1% of RGB
channels in getImageData output. This makes canvas fingerprinting
produce different results across workspaces while remaining visually
imperceptible.

The noise function (PureCloakCanvasNoise) uses the PureCloak PRNG
with a deterministic seed, ensuring the same canvas always produces
the same noise within a workspace.

No BUILDFLAG guards are needed since patches only apply during
PureCloak builds.

---
 .../canvas/canvas2d/base_rendering_context_2d.cc         | 31 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 31 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/base_rendering_context_2d.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/base_rendering_context_2d.cc
index 1c0b0b8e85..33a3493a9e 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/base_rendering_context_2d.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/canvas/canvas2d/base_rendering_context_2d.cc
@@ -100,6 +100,8 @@
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/forward.h"
 #include "third_party/blink/renderer/platform/wtf/math_extras.h"
